        <body>       
                
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Jewish Theological Seminary Association.<lb/>
                All Communications to be addressed to the Secretary&#44;<lb/>
                <del>No. 237 Broadway</del>&#44;<lb/>
                151 East 73<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> St<lb/></p>
            <p>We have no Talmud Teacher<lb/> yet&#45;&#45;Dr Mendes is looking<lb/> after the matter&#45;&#45;<lb/>
                JOSEPH BLUMENTHAL&#44; President&#44;<lb/>
                DR. A. FRIEDENWALD&#44; V. President&#44;<lb/>
                NEWMAN COWEN&#44; Treasurer&#44;<lb/>
                JOSEPH E. NEWBURGER&#44; Secretary.<lb/></p>
            <p>New York&#44; April 6<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1887<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev S. Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>Your kind favor of the 28<hi rend="sup">th</hi><lb/> ult. came duly to hand&#44; and I was pleased to see<lb/> therefrom that you have organised your branch of<lb/> the association&#45;&#45;I doubt not good results will<lb/> follow&#45;&#45;I received a letter from Mr Lederer your<lb/> Secretary&#44; and in conjunction with Max Cohen<lb/> gave him all the documents&#44; information &#38;c<lb/> that he asked for&#45;&#45;I hope you will now at last<lb/> get your city Patrons and Subscribers in better<lb/> shape as to their payments &#38;c. than has been<lb/> the case thus far&#44; while the accounts have been<lb/> kept here&#45;&#45;the full lists have been sent to<lb/> Mr Lederer&#44; and if there are any mistakes or<lb/> omissions you can correct them&#45;&#45;I have<lb/> now replied to your letter ere this for the reason<lb/> that I desired to await some developments as<lb/> to our remaining at 19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> St&#44; which for awhile<lb/> looked more uncertain&#45;&#45;in fact Mr Phillips<lb/> had given us notice to vacate&#44; and interdicted<lb/> our having classes during this and next week&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>this would have been most unfortunate not only&#44;<lb/> but out of the question for us&#45;&#45;by much patience<lb/> some diplomacy&#44; and by the support of three other<lb/> Trustees of the Congregation&#44; not only that diffi&#61;<lb/>culty has been overcome&#44; but we shall have<lb/> the use of same&#44; for the Entire term&#44; or until<lb/> July 1<hi rend="sup">st</hi>&#45;&#45;so you see how vastly productive of<lb/> good and useful&#44; your interviewing Mr Wallach<lb/> &#38; Mr Levy was&#45;&#45;it saves aside from the necessity<lb/> of charging fifty dollars per month from now<lb/> until the beginning of our next term&#44; say about<lb/> Sept 1<hi rend="sup">st</hi>&#45;&#45;as I hope to see you certainly after<lb/> the Holidays&#44; I will then explain all more<lb/> fully&#45;&#45;Dr Drachman and the class&#44; seem to be<lb/> getting along satisfactorily&#45;&#45;I think he is the best<lb/> choice we could have made&#45;&#45;respecting the future<lb/> &#38;c&#44; I shall act cautiously and prudently as you<lb/> suggest&#45;&#45;we shall have another meeting next<lb/> week looking towards some energetic action in favor<lb/> of the Seminary &#38;c&#45;&#45;I hope it will prove a success&#45;<lb/>will you kindly inform me whether you would<lb/> prefer to come here usually by the Pennsylvania<lb/> or the other road&#45;&#45;the terms will be the same&#44;<lb/> so we had better use the most convenient&#44; if<lb/> I can make arrangements&#45;&#45;let me know when<lb/> you are coming&#44; as I wish to see you&#45;&#45;Hoping you<lb/> will enjoy the approaching festival &#38;c&#44; Yours sincerely<lb/> Joseph Blumenthal<lb/></p>
            </body>
